item.title: Can someone teamview me?
item.dc:creator: @expozee expozee
item.description:
@expozee wrote:

[quote=“iCharizard, post:7, topic:393252”][quote author=expozee link=topic=490419.msg3586311#msg3586311 date=1304207783]

Do you have a static Ip set up?

what’s a static ip?
[/quote]

You could’ve easily of figured this out your self by searching here. Expozee, can you describe in detail how you portforwarded to assure me you did it correctly.

@jmk it’s not NO-IP.

[quote]Static IP Address Definition
A static IP address means your computer uses the same address every time you log on to the Internet. With a static IP address, other Internet users always know the identity of your computer and can easily connect with it. That way, you can host a website, email server, or other type of server connection.[/quote][/quote]
i had this guy teamview me and portfoward for me, i went to my router’s site, and i set up a virutal server, with a private ip and a private port, and i set the inbound port to 43594, and i made the private port to 43594
